29/04/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- Two soldiers were killed and two others were injured in a clash with members of the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) in southeast Turkey on Wednesday (April 28th), security sources said. It happened in the Semdinli district of Hakkari province. Soldiers reportedly were patrolling the area when they came across a group of militants who, rather than surrender, opened fire on them. (Zaman - 28/04/10; CNN Turk, Press TV, Reuters, Hurriyet - 27/04/10)
